# Python-Specific Rules

## Style
- Match existing style: black-formatted or not, docstring style, type hint usage
- Don't add type hints where none exist unless asked
- Don't reformat existing code while fixing something unrelated

## Output
- For single-function edits: show only that function
- For class edits: show only the changed method(s)
- Use `# ... rest of class unchanged` to skip

## Imports
- Show only net-new import lines needed
- Do not reprint the full import block

## Common shortcuts
- If a pattern repeats across methods, note it once: `# same pattern as create_x()`
- Prefer list comprehensions over loops unless the existing code uses loops
- Match existing error handling style (bare except vs specific exceptions)

## Never
- Don't add `if __name__ == "__main__"` unless asked
- Don't add logging setup unless asked
- Don't convert functions to async unless asked
